    overview: "Ventilator-associated pneumonia (VAP) is a hospital-acquired pneumonia developing ≥ 48 hours after intubation. It is the most common nosocomial infection in ICU patients, affecting 10–25% of ventilated patients, with attributable mortality of 10–15%. VAP prevention bundles are a key responsibility of respiratory therapists.",
